summary:
The Security Council,
Reaffirming resolutions 864 (1993), 1127 (1997), 1173 (1998), 1237 (1999), 1295 (2000) and 1336 (2001), 
Reaffirming commitment to preserve Angola's sovereignty and territorial integrity,
Expressing concern over humanitarian effects on civilians,
Recognizing need for monitoring implementation of resolutions,
Determining situation in Angola threatens international peace and security,
Acting under Chapter VII,
1. Takes note of addendum (S/2001/363) to final report (S/2000/1225) of monitoring mechanism;
2. Intends to consider addendum and final report;
3. Extends monitoring mechanism's mandate for six months, until 19 October 2001;
4. Requests periodic reports to Committee and supplementary report by 19 October 2001;
5. Requests Secretary-General to appoint up to five experts and make necessary financial arrangements;
6. Requests Chairman of Committee to submit supplementary report by 19 October 2001;
7. Calls for States to cooperate with monitoring mechanism;
8. Decides to remain seized of the matter.
